  <div class="row q3">
    <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12">       
    <h2>What are some challenges you faced?</h2>     
    </div>  
    <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12">      
      <p>
         Being completed within a few days the application is far from perfect. One of the challenges I faced was displaying
         only the journal entries that the user posted and not others' entries as well. I think this may be because of the NoSQL
         database. Since there are little to no options when it comes to setting up relationships between collections in a NoSQL
         model, the better option may could be a standard relational database. Because of this flaw users can see all journal entires,
         not just their own. 
      </p>
      <p>
         Another challenge was the time constraint. I would have also liked to add sign in with Google or Facebook, however due
         to the limited time on the project, I was unable to complete that functionality, opting to stick with a standard database check.
      </p>      
